    "In this landscape, data acquisition and image processing emerge as a critical domain of local neural circuits, i.e., spatially colocalized neurons of the same kind or with shared organizational traits (Bohland et al., 2009).",
    "It also generates a huge amount of data to be processed and may not be as easily quantifiable (Lang et al., 2012; Chen et al., 2019).",
    "Currently, artificial intelligence algorithms have proved their ability to help researchers in image processing and analysis: from contrast enhancement/normalization to segmentation and extraction of morphological features necessary for structural correlation of connectivity (Durkee et al., 2021).",
    "As stated above, neuroimaging encompasses a diverse array of techniques for exploring different scales of magnitude and activities within cells and tissues.",
    "Consequently, data analyses are predominantly linked to the complexities of the images, posing a challenge for neuroscientists who may not be familiar with the intricacies of the field."
